staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000100=So I was thinking about how we could improve the local farmlands.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000200=Our first step should be to improve crop yield.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000300=After that we'll try out this new formula I invented...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000400=Are you even listening?
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000500=Just the other day I rolled out a new cultivator.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000600=I was going to show you but the mayor confiscated it...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000700=And here it would have made your work so much easier too...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000800=Don't go drinking bottles you find lying around...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10000900=Some of those chemicals do nasty things to a person.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001000=Not that I'm speaking from experience of course...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001100=^c:d03e37;Seedmakers^c:pop; are fantastic aren't they?
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001200=Sometimes you can end up with rare variants!
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001300=I wonder if I can rig one to produce them more often...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001400=Just to be clear...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001500=It's professor, not doctor.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001600=Professor ^c:1486b0;{0-name}^c:pop;.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001700=Don't mix them up.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001800=^c:1486b0;{0-shopkeep}^c:pop; has been giving me strange looks recently...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10001900=Did I do something to cause offence?
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002000=I'm a bit sceptical about that magic water...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002100=I don't know where it came from or how it works...
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002200=But, there's no way magic is a real thing.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002300=How do airships work, you ask?
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002400=Well then! That's a fascinating topic.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002500=You see, we build the hull from an ultralight super-material.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002600=The rotors-
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002700=Wood? What? Where did you hear that?
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002800=It just looks like wood! It's not really wood!
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10002900=There's no such thing as magic!
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003000=Rainy days are such a great energy saver!
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003100=I can turn off all my sprinkler systems.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003200=The rain does all the watering for me!
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003300=If you want to know how the lights work, I can't help you.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003400=Countless research projects have proven fruitless.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003500=We disproved the existence of the luminiferous aether.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003600=There is no light emitting photon energy source.
staxel.village.dialogue.Scientist.line:10003700=And it is definitely. Not. Magic.
